pm run build (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — code-review (2026-04-04T03:01)\n\n- MEDIUM: `VALID_TRANSITIONS` key type was `string` instead of constrained union — fixed with `TransitionableStatus`.\n- MEDIUM: Non-deterministic story ordering from `getEpicStories` — fixed with `.sort()`.\n- MEDIUM: Missing runtime test for `failed` as terminal state — added test.\n- MEDIUM: Unsafe cast in `transitionEpicState` VALID_TRANSITIONS lookup — fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): `TransitionableStatus` not exported. Acceptable for now.\n- LOW (unfixed): `EpicCompletionError` lacks structured metadata fields.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest coverage (~60 lines), git diff --name-only (~18 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (epic-completion.ts read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: one extra grep for coverage output\n\n### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — verification (2026-04-04T03:05)\n\n- Proof format issues: `### AC N:` headers needed `## AC N:`, `**Result:**` needed `**Verdict:**`, and `Tier:` needed `**Tier:**`. Fixed manually by orchestrator.\n- `codeharness verify` precondition failure: AGENTS.md stale for `src/lib` — fixed by adding epic-completion.ts entry.\n- Lint: 8 errors, 58 warnings pre-existing, none in story files.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14 (verifier) + 3 retries (orchestrator format fixes)\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~50 lines), npm run lint (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: test:coverage ran twice\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (session 5)\n\n### 19-2-epic-flow-execution — create-story (2026-04-04T03:16)\n\n- No problems encountered — epic definition clear, dependency chain clean.\n- Risk: AC #3 retro step uses optional `dispatchRetro` callback — dependency injection point, not full integration.\n- Risk: AC #10 lane freeing tested indirectly via promise resolution.\n- Observation: Final story in epic 19. Validate step may be redundant with merge validation.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 4, Glob: 4, Write: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 19-2-epic-flow-execution — dev-story (2026-04-04T03:24)\n\n- State machine gap: `epic-completion.ts` doesn't allow `completing -> done` directly. Empty/retro-only flows use `validating` initial state — subtle coupling between executor and caller.\n- No logging in retro skip path — no logger dependency available. Minor gap.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 11, Bash: 4, Grep: 2, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest run (~60 lines), npm test (~30 lines), npm run build (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 19-2-epic-flow-execution — code-review (2026-04-04T03:33)\n\n- HIGH: Empty epicFlow array attempted invalid `completing → done` transition — would throw at runtime. Fixed with EMPTY_FLOW_TRANSITIONS constant.\n- MEDIUM: `result.reason ?? 'unknown'` fallback branch untested. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `String(err)` coercion branch untested. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): Retro-only flow tests still use `validating` initial state — workaround comment could be cleaner.\n- LOW (unfixed): `executeStep` switch should become step registry if more types added.\n- Architecture: EMPTY_FLOW_TRANSITIONS hardcodes state machine path — no compile-time coupling to `epic-completion.ts`.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 8, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage table (~30 lines), npm test (~8 lines), vitest run (~8 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 12 total reads (epic-flow-executor.ts read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: none\n","numLines":274,"startLine":1,"totalLines":274}}}
