{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011dUZPVxLV839ZxPjGhYKoh","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2]\n3\tstatus: complete\n4\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-03'\n5\tinputDocuments:\n6\t  - prd.md (parallel execution PRD)\n7\t  - ux-design-specification.md (existing CLI UX v2)\n8\t  - architecture-multi-framework.md (TUI component architecture)\n9\tworkflowType: 'ux-design'\n10\tnote: 'Multi-lane TUI UX for parallel epic execution, merge status, and telemetry visibility'\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\t# TUI UX Specification — Parallel Execution Extension\n14\t\n15\t**Date:** 2026-04-03\n16\t**Extends:** ux-design-specification.md (CLI UX v2)\n17\t\n18\t## Overview\n19\t\n20\tThis extends the existing CLI UX patterns for parallel execution. The core addition: the TUI goes from a single-lane view (one story at a time) to a **multi-lane view** (multiple epics executing concurrently in separate worktrees). All existing patterns (status prefixes, symbols, progressive detail, dense output) remain unchanged.\n21\t\n22\t**New UX surfaces:**\n23\t1. Multi-lane TUI rendering during `codeharness run --live`\n24\t2. Merge status and conflict resolution display\n25\t3. Lane lifecycle visualization (create → execute → merge → cleanup)\n26\t4. Telemetry visibility (optional, not in default view)\n27\t5. Updated `codeharness status` for parallel runs\n28\t\n29\t## Design Principles (Inherited + Extended)\n30\t\n31\tAll 8 existing principles apply. New additions:\n32\t\n33\t9. **Lanes are independent.** Each lane is self-contained — a failure in lane 1 doesn't pollute lane 2's display.\n34\t10. **Merge is a first-class event.** Merge attempts, conflicts, resolutions, and test results are visible — not hidden in logs.\n35\t11. **Parallel ≠ noisy.** Two lanes should be as readable as one lane was. Compress, don't duplicate.\n36\t\n37\t## Multi-Lane Live Mode: `codeharness run --live`\n38\t\n39\t### Two Parallel Lanes (Default: max_parallel=2)\n40\t\n41\t```\n42\tcodeharness run | 2 lanes | 47m elapsed | $18.60 spent\n43\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n44\t Lane 1: Epic 10 — Driver Interface         Lane 2: Epic 14 — TUI Workflow\n45\t 10-3 ◆ dev (AC 4/9)                        14-1 ◆ verify (AC 2/6)\n46\t ✓ 10-1  ✓ 10-2  ◆ 10-3  ○ 10-4  ○ 10-5   ◆ 14-1  ○ 14-2  ○ 14-3\n47\t claude-code | $4.20 / 18m                   codex | $1.30 / 8m\n48\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n49\tDone: 10-1 ✓  10-2 ✓ │ Merging: — │ Pending: epic-11, epic-12, epic-13, epic-15\n50\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n51\t ✓ Read src/lib/agents/drivers/types.ts\n52\t ⚡ Edit src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts ◌\n53\t```\n54\t\n55\t### Layout Rules\n56\t\n57\t**Header line:** `codeharness run | {N} lanes | {elapsed} | ${cost}`\n58\t\n59\t**Lane columns:**\n60\t- Two lanes render side-by-side (half terminal width each)\n61\t- Three+ lanes: top 2 active lanes shown, others collapsed to one-line summaries below\n62\t- Each lane shows: epic title, current story + phase + AC progress, story progress bar, driver + cost/time\n63\t\n64\t**Summary bar:** Between lanes and activity. Shows: done count, merge status, pending epics.\n65\t\n66\t**Activity section:** Shows the MOST RECENTLY ACTIVE lane's tool/thought/retry. Only one activity stream at a time — the one that last produced output. Prefixed with lane number.\n67\t\n68\t### Three or More Lanes\n69\t\n70\t```\n71\tcodeharness run | 3 lanes | 1h12m elapsed | $32.10 spent\n72\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n73\t Lane 1: Epic 10 — Driver Interface         Lane 2: Epic 14 — TUI Workflow\n74\t 10-4 ◆ verify (AC 3/7)                     14-2 ◆ dev\n75\t ✓ 10-1  ✓ 10-2  ✓ 10-3  ◆ 10-4  ○ 10-5   ✓ 14-1  ◆ 14-2  ○ 14-3\n76\t claude-code | $6.80 / 32m                   codex | $2.10 / 14m\n77\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n78\t Lane 3: Epic 11 — Workflow Schema │ 11-1 ◆ dev │ $0.40 / 2m\n79\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n80\tDone: 10-1 ✓  10-2 ✓  10-3 ✓  14-1 ✓ │ Merging: — │ Pending: epic-12, epic-13\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\tLane 3+ collapse to a single line: `Lane N: Epic Title │ story ◆ phase │ $cost / time`\n84\t\n85\t### Single Lane (Backward Compatible)\n86\t\n87\tWhen `max_parallel: 1` or only one epic remains:\n88\t\n89\t```\n90\tcodeharness run | iteration 3 | 47m elapsed | $12.30 spent\n91\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n92\tStory: 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching\n93\tPhase: verify → AC 8/12\n94\t\n95\tDone: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓\n96\tThis: 3-2 ◆ verifying (8/12 ACs)\n97\tNext: 3-3\n98\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n99\t```\n100\t\n101\tIdentical to current single-lane UX. No visual changes.\n102\t\n103\t## Merge Status Display\n104\t\n105\t### Merge In Progress\n106\t\n107\tWhen an epic completes and merges:\n108\t\n109\t```\n110\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n111\tDone: 10-1 ✓ ... │ Merging: epic-14 → main ◌ │ Pending: epic-11, epic-12\n112\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n113\t```\n114\t\n115\t### Merge Successful (Clean)\n116\t\n117\t```\n118\t[OK] Merge epic-14 → main: clean (0 conflicts)\n119\t[OK] Tests: 1650/1650 passed (18s)\n120\t[OK] Worktree cleaned: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-14\n121\t[INFO] Lane 2 → picking up epic-11\n122\t```\n123\t\n124\t### Merge Conflict — Agent Resolving\n125\t\n126\t```\n127\t[WARN] Merge epic-11 → main: 1 conflict in src/lib/workflow-engine.ts\n128\t[INFO] Dispatching merge agent...\n129\t```\n130\t\n131\tSummary bar updates:\n132\t\n133\t```\n134\tDone: ... │ Merging: epic-11 → main (resolving 1 conflict) ◌ │ Pending: ...\n135\t```\n136\t\n137\t### Merge Conflict — Resolved\n138\t\n139\t```\n140\t[OK] Merge epic-11 → main: 1 conflict auto-resolved\n141\t     └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: additive changes in different functions\n142\t[OK] Tests: 1652/1652 passed (19s)\n143\t[OK] Worktree cleaned: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-11\n144\t```\n145\t\n146\t### Merge Conflict — Escalated\n147\t\n148\t```\n149\t[FAIL] Merge epic-11 → main: conflict unresolvable after 3 attempts\n150\t       └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: semantic conflict in dispatchTaskWithResult()\n151\t       └ Epic 10 refactored function signature, epic 11 added parameters\n152\t       → Manual resolution required\n153\t       → Worktree preserved: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-11\n154\t       → Branch: codeharness/epic-11-workflow-schema\n155\t       → Run: cd /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-11 && git diff main\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\t### Cross-Worktree Test Validation\n159\t\n160\tAfter merge, before cleanup:\n161\t\n162\t```\n163\t[INFO] Running cross-worktree test validation on merged result...\n164\t[OK] Tests: 1652/1652 passed (19s)\n165\t[OK] Coverage: 96.8% (target: 90%)\n166\t```\n167\t\n168\tIf tests fail after merge:\n169\t\n170\t```\n171\t[FAIL] Cross-worktree test validation failed after merge\n172\t       └ 3 tests failed in src/lib/workflow-engine.test.ts\n173\t       └ Merge conflict resolution may have introduced regression\n174\t       → Reverting merge: git reset --hard HEAD~1\n175\t       → Dispatching merge agent with test failure context (attempt 2/3)\n176\t```\n177\t\n178\t## Updated `codeharness status` — Parallel Run\n179\t\n180\t### Active Parallel Run\n181\t\n182\t```\n183\tcodeharness v0.27.0 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n184\t\n185\t── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n186\tSprint: 31/47 done (66%) | 11/15 epics complete\n187\tActive epics: 10, 14 (parallel, 2 lanes)\n188\tModules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n189\t\n190\t── Active Run (parallel) ─────────────────────────────────────\n191\tStatus: running (2 lanes, 1h12m elapsed)\n192\tLane 1: Epic 10 → 10-4 verifying (AC 3/7) | $6.80\n193\tLane 2: Epic 14 → 14-2 dev | $2.10\n194\tTotal cost: $32.10 | 16 stories remaining\n195\t\n196\t── This Run ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n197\tCompleted:  7 stories (10-1..10-3, 14-1, 11-1..11-2, 12-1)\n198\tMerged:     2 epics (epic-11 clean, epic-12 clean)\n199\tConflicts:  0 auto-resolved, 0 escalated\n200\tFailed:     0 stories\n201\tIn progress: 2 stories (10-4, 14-2)\n202\t\n203\t── Worktrees ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n204\t Active: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-10 (branch: codeharness/epic-10)\n205\t Active: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-14 (branch: codeharness/epic-14)\n206\t Cleaned: 2 (epic-11, epic-12)\n207\t```\n208\t\n209\t## Lane Lifecycle Events\n210\t\n211\t### Lane Created\n212\t\n213\t```\n214\t[INFO] Lane 1: creating worktree for epic-10 (5 stories)\n215\t[OK] Worktree: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-10\n216\t[OK] Branch: codeharness/epic-10-driver-interface\n217\t[INFO] Lane 1: starting 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types\n218\t```\n219\t\n220\t### Lane Completed (Epic Done)\n221\t\n222\t```\n223\t[OK] Lane 2: Epic 14 complete (3/3 stories, $3.40, 22m)\n224\t[INFO] Running epic retro...\n225\t[OK] Retro: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-14-retrospective.md\n226\t[INFO] Merging epic-14 → main...\n227\t[OK] Merge: clean | Tests: 1652 passed\n228\t[OK] Worktree cleaned\n229\t[INFO] Lane 2 → picking up epic-15 (3 stories)\n230\t```\n231\t\n232\t### All Lanes Finished\n233\t\n234\t```\n235\t[OK] All epics complete. Sprint done.\n236\t     └ 6 epics | 19 stories | 4h12m | $245.30\n237\t     └ Merges: 6 (5 clean, 1 auto-resolved)\n238\t     └ Worktrees: 0 active, 6 cleaned\n239\t```\n240\t\n241\t## Telemetry Display\n242\t\n243\tTelemetry is **invisible by default** — it's infrastructure, not user-facing. The data feeds into epic retros and `codeharness stats`.\n244\t\n245\t### Optional: `codeharness stats --telemetry`\n246\t\n247\t```\n248\t── Session Telemetry ──────────────────────────────────────────\n249\tEntries: 19 stories | Source: .codeharness/telemetry.jsonl\n250\t\n251\tBy Epic:\n252\t  Epic 10: 5 stories | $18.20 | 42m | 2 retries\n253\t  Epic 11: 2 stories | $5.10  | 12m | 0 retries\n254\t  Epic 12: 3 stories | $9.40  | 21m | 1 retry\n255\t  Epic 13: 3 stories | $8.60  | 19m | 0 retries\n256\t  Epic 14: 3 stories | $3.40  | 14m | 0 retries\n257\t  Epic 15: 3 stories | $4.20  | 16m | 1 retry\n258\t\n259\tMost expensive story: 10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction ($5.80)\n260\tMost retries: 10-5-workflow-engine-driver-integration (2 retries)\n261\t```\n262\t\n263\t## Color Coding\n264\t\n265\tExtends existing scheme:\n266\t\n267\t| Element | Color | Context |\n268\t|---------|-------|---------|\n269\t| Lane header | white bold | Lane separator |\n270\t| Lane number | cyan | Active lane indicator |\n271\t| Merge in progress | yellow | Merging status |\n272\t| Merge clean | green | Successful merge |\n273\t| Merge conflict | red | Conflict detected |\n274\t| Merge resolved | green | Auto-resolved |\n275\t| Merge escalated | red bold | Manual intervention needed |\n276\t| Test pass (post-merge) | green | Cross-worktree validation |\n277\t| Test fail (post-merge) | red bold | Regression detected |\n278\t| Worktree active | dim cyan | Active worktree path |\n279\t| Worktree cleaned | dim | Cleaned worktree |\n280\t\n281\t## Component Architecture\n282\t\n283\t### New Ink Components\n284\t\n285\t```\n286\t<App>\n287\t  <Header />                    # Extended: lane count, total cost across lanes\n288\t  <Separator />\n289\t  <LaneContainer>               # NEW: manages lane layout\n290\t    <Lane epic={10}>            # NEW: one per active worktree\n291\t      <WorkflowGraph />         # From multi-framework PRD\n292\t      <StoryProgress />\n293\t    </Lane>\n294\t    <Lane epic={14}>\n295\t      <WorkflowGraph />\n296\t      <StoryProgress />\n297\t    </Lane>\n298\t    <CollapsedLanes />          # NEW: one-line summaries for lanes 3+\n299\t  </LaneContainer>\n300\t  <Separator />\n301\t  <SummaryBar />                # NEW: done, merging, pending\n302\t  <Separator />\n303\t  <MergeStatus />               # NEW: merge progress, conflicts, test results\n304\t  <ActivityDisplay />           # Existing: shows most recently active lane\n305\t</App>\n306\t```\n307\t\n308\t### Layout Responsiveness\n309\t\n310\t- **Terminal width >= 120 cols:** Two lanes side-by-side\n311\t- **Terminal width 80-119 cols:** Two lanes stacked vertically (compact mode)\n312\t- **Terminal width < 80 cols:** Single active lane only, others collapsed\n313\t\n314\t## Interaction Patterns\n315\t\n316\t### `Ctrl+L` — Cycle Active Lane Display\n317\t\n318\tWhen multiple lanes are active, `Ctrl+L` cycles which lane's activity stream is shown in the bottom activity section. Visual indicator: `[Lane 1 ▸]` or `[Lane 2 ▸]` in the activity header.\n319\t\n320\t### `Ctrl+M` — Toggle Merge Detail\n321\t\n322\tWhen a merge is in progress, `Ctrl+M` expands/collapses merge detail in the merge status section. Default: collapsed (one-line summary). Expanded: full conflict list, agent output, test results.\n323\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AgQJFigSq3KJGDuPKevuMV","session_id":"568bb8a3-7cec-4d55-8fe6-c91654e95e9c","uuid":"691e5913-cf21-47a0-8244-470ad09366ca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:46:11.885Z"}
